</span></h2><p class="sc-gyElHZ hUTxLq pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-37_">As you will like to dress up perfectly in a yellow saree to impress your beau – the choice of the material is also a huge factor. There are huge choices, but predominantly, it is the tant, cotton, dhakai, and tussar, which are sure to win many hearts. Pick something light to wear on this eve. You can also pick a range of Kantha stitch, batik, or pure handlooms. Here is a list of the type of sarees for you:<br><br><b>Dhakai Jamdani Sarees: </b>There are three types of <a href="/collections/dhakai-jamdani-sarees" target="_blank">Jamdani sarees</a>: a butidar sari (an entire sari covered in florals), a tercha sari (a diagonal pattern of florals), and a jhalar sari (a floral network). The weave originated in Bangladesh (formerly undivided Bengal). Jamdani weavers can be found in West Bengal, Andhra Pradesh, Maharashtra, Rajasthan, and Uttar Pradesh.<br><br><b>Tussar Silk Sarees:</b>
A dull gold thread is used to embroider and print designs that are inspired by nature. Wide-winged moths produce this yellowish-brown moth. <a href="/collections/tussar-silk" target="_blank">Tussar silk</a> weaves can also be used to create floral patterns and motifs, including flowers, leaves, and leaflets on a yellow silk saree.<br><br><b>Chanderi Silk Sarees: </b>The yellow <a href="/collections/chanderi-silk-saree" target="_blank">Chanderi silk saree</a> is available in a wide variety of styles online, with a silk warp and cotton wefts woven in a multi-wefting technique. Its primary market is Madhya Pradesh, but Kolkata, West Bengal is also a major market for Chanderi sarees.<br><br><b>Bishnupur Silk Sarees:</b>
